</div></div><a href="#" class="closebtn">×</a></div></div></div><div class="site-inner"><div class="content-sidebar-wrap"><main class="content" id="genesis-content"><nav id="breadcrumbs" aria-label="breadcrumbs"><span><span><a href="https://cookwithdana.com/">Cook With Dana</a></span> » <span><a href="https://cookwithdana.com/recipes/">Recipes</a></span> » <span><a href="https://cookwithdana.com/category/recipes/side-dishes/">Side Dishes</a></span></span></nav><p class="entry-meta">Updated: <time class="entry-modified-time">Feb 3, 2026</time> · by <span class="entry-author"><a href="https://cookwithdana.com/about/" class="entry-author-link" rel="author"><span class="entry-author-name">Dana Rao</span></a></span> · This post may contain affiliate links · <span class="entry-comments-link"><a href="https://cookwithdana.com/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu/#comments">1 Comment</a></span>																				</p><article class="post-14494 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-korean-recipes category-meals-under-30-minutes category-side-dishes entry" aria-label="Korean Spicy Marinated Tofu"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title">Korean Spicy Marinated Tofu</h1>
</header><div class="entry-content"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-snippet wprm-recipe-template-no-jump-to-video"><a href="#recipe" data-recipe="14594" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #000000;border-color: #333333;border-radius: 3px;padding: 5px 8px;" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-jump-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-jump-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" fill="#ffffff"><path data-color="color-2" d="M9,2h6c0.6,0,1-0.4,1-1s-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,0,8,0.4,8,1S8.4,2,9,2z"></path> <path fill="#ffffff" d="M16,11V5c0-0.6-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,4,8,4.4,8,5v6H1.9L12,23.6L22.1,11H16z"></path></g></svg></span> Jump to Recipe</a>

<a href="https://cookwithdana.com/wprm_print/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #000000;border-color: #333333;border-radius: 3px;padding: 5px 8px;" class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-print-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent" data-recipe-id="14594" data-template="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#ffffff" d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.569,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18.552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print Recipe</a></div>
<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>Make this <em>10 minute</em> <strong><em>Korean Spicy Marinated Tofu</em></strong> inspired by Korean Yangnyeom sauce for your next weeknight dinner or meal prep. This dish is super flavorful (sweet and spicy) that will turn tofu haters (like my husband) into tofu lovers!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1600" src="https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu-firstphoto.jpg" alt="Sliced silken tofu in a spicy, savory Korean sauce topped with green onions and sesame seeds, served over rice." class="wp-image-14607" srcset="https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu-firstphoto.jpg 1200w, https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu-firstphoto-225x300.jpg 225w, https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu-firstphoto-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu-firstphoto-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu-firstphoto-720x960.jpg 720w, https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu-firstphoto-360x480.jpg 360w, https://cookwithdana.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/korean-spicy-marinated-tofu-firstphoto-180x240.jpg 180w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-group is-style-default has-background" style="background-color:#ebdbeb"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 id="%f0%9f%94%8d-quick-look"   class="wp-block-heading" >🔍 Quick Look:&nbsp;</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>What is it?</strong>&nbsp;Silken tofu marinated in a Korean sweet and spicy sauce inspired by the popular <em>Yangnyeom (means spicy sauce</em>) flavor that is used to season Korean raw marinated crab.  If you’re a tofu fan, my <a href="https://cookwithdana.com/vegetarian-mapo-tofu/">Easy Mapo Tofu</a> or <a href="https://cookwithdana.com/korean-braised-tofu-dubu-jorim/">Korean Braised Tofu</a> is a quick and flavorful addition to your must-try recipes.</li>



<li><strong>Why you’ll love this recipe:</strong>&nbsp;You can make this tofu dish in less than 10 minutes! The sweet and spicy flavor is good on anything –noodles, rice and toast! A protein packed dish that is perfect for a busy weeknight or make a large batch for meal prep. </li>



<li>🕒&nbsp;<strong>Total Cook Time:</strong>&nbsp;5 minutes</li>



<li>🔥&nbsp;<strong>Cook Method:</strong>&nbsp;Just boil the silken tofu for 2 minutes, drain it well, then add the Korean sauce on top. The tofu tastes best marinated overnight to soak up the flavor, yet still tastes super delicious if you eat right away. </li>



<li>👩‍🍳&nbsp;<strong>Flavor Profile:</strong>&nbsp;This dish is spicy, savory, and slightly sweet. The creamy tofu that soaks up the umami flavor from the sauce.</li>



<li>⭐&nbsp;<strong>Difficulty:</strong>&nbsp;Super easy! Just boil the tofu, marinate it, then enjoy it with hot rice, noodles or your favorite veggies.</li>
</ul>



<p><strong>Summarize &amp; Save this content on:</strong></p>
</div></div>
</div></div>


